      "question": "A team of surveyors is measuring the height of a vertical communication tower $AB$ standing on level ground. From a point $P$ on the ground, the angle of elevation of the top $A$ is $60^\\circ$. Moving $40$ $m$ further away from the tower along the same straight line to a point $Q$, the angle of elevation of the top $A$ is found to be $30^\\circ$. The base $B$ is between $P$ and $Q$.",
      "type": "case_study",
